# Validex Design System

## Stack
Next.js 16 · App Router · Tailwind v4 · TypeScript · GSAP + Lenis · `next/font/google`

---

## Colour Tokens (globals.css :root)

| Token | Value | Use |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `--paper` | `#F2EEE4` | Primary background (warm bone) |
| `--paper-deep` | `#E7E1D3` | Alt light surface, cards on light bg |
| `--ink` | `#15130E` | Primary text, dark section bg |
| `--ink-soft` | `#232019` | Dark card surfaces, scorecard bg |
| `--moss` | `#2E5E3E` | Primary accent — use SPARINGLY |
| `--moss-bright` | `#4A8A5E` | Hover / active states only |
| `--on-dark` | `rgba(242,238,228,0.62)` | Body text on dark sections |
| `--on-light` | `rgba(21,19,14,0.60)` | Body text on light sections |
| `--line-dark` | `rgba(242,238,228,0.12)` | Borders / dividers on dark bg |
| `--line-light` | `rgba(21,19,14,0.10)` | Borders / dividers on light bg |

**Never use** raw hex values for colours — always use tokens via `var(--token)`.
**Never use** pure `#000000` or `#ffffff` — use `var(--ink)` and `var(--paper)`.
**`--moss` accent** — one prominent use per section maximum.

---

## Typography

### Fonts
- **DM Sans** (`var(--font-main)`) — all display, headings, body copy
- **DM Mono** (`var(--font-mono)`) — eyebrows, labels, index numbers, tags, meta, scorecard rows, footer

Both loaded via `next/font/google` in `app/layout.tsx` with CSS variables. Never import fonts elsewhere.

### Type Scale
```css
--h1:   clamp(4rem, 11vw, 12rem)   /* weight 500, tracking -0.035em, lh 0.92 */
--h2:   clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5.5rem) /* weight 500, tracking -0.03em,  lh 0.98 */
--stat: clamp(7rem, 18vw, 19rem)   /* weight 500, tracking -0.04em,  lh 0.85 */
--body: 1.0625rem                  /* weight 400, lh 1.6 */
```

### Eyebrow / Label Pattern (mono)
```tsx
<span className="who-eyebrow">§ 01 — Who We Are</span>
// font-family: var(--font-mono), size 0.72rem, tracking 0.16em, uppercase, color var(--moss)
```

### Display Headlines
```tsx
// Apply these to all h1/h2:
font-feature-settings: "ss01", "cv01";
text-rendering: optimizeLegibility;
font-weight: 500; // NOT 700 at large scale
```

